flowRoot.flowPara: You might have noticed the towering pile of waste at the corner of our basement parking that is growing by the day. The reason for this is our failure to organize our garbage according to the orders of Karnataka High Court for waste segregation at source:
Houses should use green bin for putting wet (biodegradable) waste, red bin for hazardous and sanitary waste and a reusable bag for dry (non-biodegradable) waste.
With immediate effect the housekeeping staff will only collect household waste that is segregated according to following categories and kept in an appropriate container.
Waste in plastic cover/trash bags will no longer be collected. Please educate all house members, domestic help accordingly.
For assistance please contact the association office, or Arun or Shreyas in flat 1020
